Friend of mine wrote an essay on the Internet as a "psychic" domain, designed without man's soul in mind (e.g. surviving in wilderness means one cannot sin much, as he is occupied all day w/ harvesting roots, mushrooms, brewing pine needles; chimp in nature never jerks off, etc.)

It's easy to see the old Internet of early Wikipedia, hyperlinked sites seemingly designed on Microsoft Word, Urth dot net email groups, etc. were in many ways far more advanced/cindy than today's stepped-back normie TikTok/IG that resemble stage illusion and seek to "mesmerize".

I think the steps to tame Ahriman (and not turn technology into a totem) today include: using Linux OS, using desktop over laptop, building your own PC (if able to), putting a covering over the black-mirror screen and turning your Wi-Fi off at night, f.lux.

Essay is 2 pages.
"Girls are allowed to continue to use TikTok"

Few nights ago I was just sitting on the chair, bouncing a tennis ball off the wall while in idle thought, when I realized my neighbor was doing renovations and hammering something on the other side. It puzzled me, as it was like 2 AM. Was he insane to do repairs at that hour?

Then I realized he was not actually doing renovations, but hitting at his wall in anger, as the sound of my bouncing tennis ball was annoying him and preventing him from being able to sleep. It made me think how things in life often are not like they seem at first. Lesson in here
